The shrine building was destroyed along with 1,000 homes in Ōshioya Village during the {{ill|Meiō earthquake|ja|明応地震|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Meiō earthquake|qq=}} on August 25, 1498 (Julian calendar: September 11, 1498)<ref name="km"/>. It was later rebuilt in 1644 (Kan'ei 21) and has survived to the present day<ref name="km"/>.
== Access == * By Bus: About a 7-minute walk (approximately 600 m) from the "Tokuda" bus stop or about a 9-minute walk (approximately 750 m) from the "Nishimachi" bus stop serviced by {{ill|Mie Kotsu|ja|三重交通|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Mie Kotsu|qq=}} buses. * By Car: From the "Shinkai Kita" intersection on National Route 23 (Nansei Bypass), head north via {{ill|Mie Prefectural Route 748|ja|三重県道748号大湊宮町停車場線|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Mie Prefectural Route 748|qq=}}, approximately 8 minutes (about 2.9 km). There are no parking facilities nearby.
